<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 01 at 6:26PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHEASTERN MCKEAN AND
SOUTHWESTERN POTTER COUNTIES THROUGH 645 PM EDT...
At 626 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 21
miles northeast of St. Marys, moving east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Keating Summit, Sizerville and Austin.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for
north central Pennsylvania.</instruction>
